{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17657663","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17657663"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T22:32:40+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T22:32:40+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"20588"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"20588","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/20588"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"13465"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"93767"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"13465","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/13465"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"20588"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"76977"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"4914"},{"type":"tags","id":"12504"},{"type":"tags","id":"12795"},{"type":"tags","id":"12797"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"32153"},{"type":"contributions","id":"32157"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"93767","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/93767"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 45-year-old woman with a long history of asthma presents with worsening shortness of breath, purpuric rash, and peripheral neuropathy. Blood tests show marked eosinophilia. \u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following histopathological findings is most characteristic of this condition?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Pauci-immune necrotising vasculitis with scattered eosinophils","Fibrinoid necrosis of medium-sized arteries","Eosinophilic vasculitis with extravascular granulomas","Leukocytoclastic vasculitis with eosinophilic infiltration","Lymphocytic infiltration of vessel walls"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe most characteristic histopathological finding in eosinophilic granulomatosis with polyangiitis (EGPA) is \u003Cstrong\u003Eeosinophilic vasculitis with extravascular granulomas\u003C/strong\u003E. This condition, formerly known as Churg-Strauss syndrome, features three main histopathological components: necrotising vasculitis of small to medium-sized vessels, extravascular granuloma formation, and a prominent eosinophilic infiltration in both the vessel walls and surrounding tissues.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained as follows:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPauci-immune necrotising vasculitis with scattered eosinophils\u003C/strong\u003E is more characteristic of microscopic polyangiitis with some eosinophilic component, but lacks the prominent eosinophilia and granulomatous inflammation seen in EGPA.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFibrinoid necrosis of medium-sized arteries\u003C/strong\u003E is more typical of polyarteritis nodosa. While EGPA can affect medium-sized vessels, the distinctive eosinophilic infiltration and granulomas are absent in polyarteritis nodosa.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELeukocytoclastic vasculitis with eosinophilic infiltration\u003C/strong\u003E may be seen in hypersensitivity vasculitis with an allergic component, but lacks the granulomatous inflammation characteristic of EGPA.\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELymphocytic infiltration of vessel walls\u003C/strong\u003E is seen in various vasculitides but is not the predominant feature in EGPA, which is characterised by eosinophilic rather than lymphocytic infiltration.\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EEGPA typically occurs in patients with a history of asthma or allergic rhinitis and may present with peripheral blood eosinophilia, pulmonary infiltrates, and multi-organ involvement. The presence of anti-neutrophil cytoplasmic antibodies (ANCA) is variable, with approximately 40% of patients being ANCA-positive, usually with myeloperoxidase specificity.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Eosinophilic granulomatosis with polyangiitis (EGPA) is characterised by eosinophilic infiltration of blood vessels and tissues.","EGPA is a small vessel vasculitis that typically occurs in patients with a history of asthma or allergic rhinitis.","The pathological hallmarks of EGPA include necrotising vasculitis, extravascular granulomas, and tissue eosinophilia."],"references":["Mitchell RN, Halushka MK. Blood vessels. In: Kumar V, Abbas AK, Aster JC, editors. Robbins \u0026 Cotran Pathologic Basis of Disease. 10th ed. Philadelphia: Elsevier; 2020. p. 485\u2013525."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"76977"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"20588"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"76977","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/76977"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-03-22T10:08:03+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-03-22T10:08:58+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"13465"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"93767"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4914","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4914"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Blood vessels","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":"2024-10-15T20:38:03+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-10-15T